{"id":2682,"date":"2015-06-07T21:48:32","date_gmt":"2015-06-07T19:48:32","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/?p=2682"},"modified":"2015-06-07T21:51:29","modified_gmt":"2015-06-07T19:51:29","slug":"angular-scope-on-listen-to-several-events","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/2015\/06\/angular-scope-on-listen-to-several-events\/","title":{"rendered":"Angular: $scope.$on() &#8211; listen to several events"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>I found it quite strange that\u00a0AngularJS does not have possibility to watch several Angular-events, i.e.:<\/p>\n<p>[javascript]<br \/>\n$scope.$on([&#8216;user.login&#8217;, &#8216;user.logout&#8217;], callback);<br \/>\n[\/javascript]<\/p>\n<p>and\u00a0I\u00a0decided to extend $on method, to make it handle such case:<\/p>\n<p>[javascript]<br \/>\n  var $onOrigin = $rootScope.$on;<br \/>\n  $rootScope.$on = function(names, listener) {<br \/>\n    var self = this;<\/p>\n<p>    if (!angular.isArray(names)) {<br \/>\n      names = [names];<br \/>\n    }<\/p>\n<p>    names.forEach(function(name) {<br \/>\n      $onOrigin.call(self, name, listener);<br \/>\n    });<\/p>\n<p>  };<br \/>\n[\/javascript]<\/p>\n<p>Sandbox for this code you can find <a href=\"http:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/STEVER\/h6u92pe8\/\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I found it quite strange that\u00a0AngularJS does not have possibility to watch several Angular-events, i.e.: [javascript] $scope.$on([&#8216;user.login&#8217;, &#8216;user.logout&#8217;], callback); [\/javascript] and\u00a0I\u00a0decided to extend $on method, to make it handle such case: [javascript] var $onOrigin = $rootScope.$on; $rootScope.$on = function(names, listener) &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/2015\/06\/angular-scope-on-listen-to-several-events\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_sta